<%- include('partials/head', { title: 'features', metaDesc: 'every feature perch. offers — from email parsing to weekly digest to savings tracking and vendor benchmarking.' }) %>
<%- include('partials/nav') %>

<div class="page" id="main-content" role="main">

<section class="lp-section">
  <div class="wrap" style="text-align:center;padding-top:120px;padding-bottom:32px;">
    <div class="eyebrow" style="justify-content:center;">features</div>
    <h1 style="max-width:none;margin-bottom:12px;">everything perch. <em class="glow-text">can do.</em></h1>
    <p style="font-size:15px;color:var(--pencil);max-width:560px;margin:0 auto 40px;line-height:1.6;">one tool, one job. here's every capability, from parsing to verdicts to the weekly digest.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="lp-section" style="padding-top:0;">
  <div class="wrap">

    <div class="features-grid">

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">📬</div>
        <h3>email forwarding parser</h3>
        <p>forward any renewal email to your @perch.app address and our ai extracts the key fields in seconds. works with insurance quotes, subscription receipts, broadband notices, domain renewal emails, and contract letters. batch forward dozens at once.</p>
        <div class="feature-stats">
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>14</strong> supported document types</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>3 sec</strong> average parse time</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>98%</strong> extraction accuracy</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">📄</div>
        <h3>document upload parser</h3>
        <p>send pdf invoices, scanned letters, screenshots, or photos of physical mail. the same ai engine extracts dates, amounts, providers, and price changes from any format — it doesn't need to be a perfect pdf.</p>
        <div class="feature-stats">
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>pdf, jpg, png</strong> accepted</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>ocr</strong> for scanned docs</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>multi-page</strong> support</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">⚡</div>
        <h3>instant verdict engine</h3>
        <p>every item gets one of three verdicts with a clear reason. renew — price is stable, essential, go ahead. cancel — not being used, better value exists, or you don't need it. renegotiate — price jumped, call them or switch.</p>
        <div class="feature-stats">
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>renew</strong> · cancel · renegotiate</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>reason</strong> included with each</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>precedent</strong> based on market data</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">📋</div>
        <h3>weekly digest</h3>
        <p>every monday morning, a ranked summary of everything renewing this week. no charts, no graphs, no "you spent £x this month." just a list of what's coming up and what needs your attention. read it in 90 seconds flat.</p>
        <div class="feature-stats">
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>90s</strong> average read time</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>ranked</strong> by urgency</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>monday</strong> morning delivery</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">📊</div>
        <h3>price history tracking</h3>
        <p>every renewal is versioned. see what you paid last year, this year, and what the provider is offering new customers — side by side. perch. builds a time series so you can spot loyalty penalties at a glance.</p>
        <div class="feature-stats">
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>year-on-year</strong> comparison</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>provider</strong> vs market rate</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>export</strong> to csv (premium)</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">💾</div>
        <h3>savings dashboard</h3>
        <p>see exactly how much you've saved — and how — since joining perch. broken down by "cancel and kept" and "renegotiated lower." not a budget tracker. a results tracker. money you didn't spend counts.</p>
        <div class="feature-stats">
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>realised</strong> savings counter</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>potential</strong> savings forecast</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>monthly</strong> trend chart</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">🔗</div>
        <h3>vendor &amp; saas tracking</h3>
        <p>for businesses and agencies: track every saas tool, contractor, supplier, and vendor contract in one place. know who's on annual billing, who's month-to-month, and who's up for renewal this quarter. premium feature.</p>
        <div class="feature-stats">
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>unlimited</strong> vendors</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>contract</strong> terms tracked</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>notice</strong> period alerts</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">🔍</div>
        <h3>market benchmarking</h3>
        <p>for premium users: see what other perch. users in your region are paying for the same categories. aggregated, anonymised, opt-in only. gives you a genuine sense of whether your renewal is reasonable — or a ripoff.</p>
        <div class="feature-stats">
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>anonymised</strong> aggregate data</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>regional</strong> breakdowns</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>opt-in</strong> only</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">📅</div>
        <h3>calendar view</h3>
        <p>every tracked renewal plotted on a calendar so you can see at a glance what's coming up and when. colour-coded by verdict type — urgent items in gold, cancellations in red, safe renewals in green.</p>
        <div class="feature-stats">
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>colour-coded</strong> by verdict</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>month</strong> and week views</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>ical</strong> export</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">👥</div>
        <h3>team digest forwarding</h3>
        <p>for premium users with multiple inboxes: forward the team digest to your co-founder, your ops person, or your accountant. they don't need a perch. account — they just get the summary every week.</p>
        <div class="feature-stats">
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>up to 5</strong> recipients</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>read-only</strong> digest</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>per-inbox</strong> filtering</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">📥</div>
        <h3>multi-inbox forwarding</h3>
        <p>premium users get up to three dedicated @perch.app forwarding addresses — one for personal, one for family, one for business. keep them separate, see them together or individually in your dashboard.</p>
        <div class="feature-stats">
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>3 inboxes</strong> on premium</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>separate</strong> or unified view</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>auto-routing</strong> by domain</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">⚙️</div>
        <h3>deadline alerts</h3>
        <p>get nudged at 30 days, 14 days, 7 days, and 24 hours before any renewal hits. configurable per category — you might want 30 days for insurance but 7 days for a domain renewal. you control the cadence.</p>
        <div class="feature-stats">
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>4-stage</strong> nudge sequence</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>per-category</strong> config</span>
          <span class="feature-stat"><strong>email</strong> &amp; in-app alerts</span>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<section class="lp-section lp-section-dark" style="text-align:center;">
  <div class="wrap">
    <h2 style="max-width:none;margin-bottom:12px;">what perch. <em class="glow-text">doesn't</em> do.</h2>
    <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--pencil);max-width:480px;margin:0 auto 0;line-height:1.6;">no bank linking · no budget charts · no credit scores · no auto-cancelling · no referral harvesting · no dark patterns · no free-tier data mining · no "sync your calendar" prompts · no upsell notifications · no pushy emails</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="final-cta lp-section">
    <div class="wrap" style="position:relative;">
    <h2>one job.<br><span class="glow-text">done right.</span></h2>
    <p>everything renews. perch. helps you see it coming.</p>
    <div class="final-cta-row">
      <a href="/waitlist" class="btn-primary">get early access →</a>
      <a href="/demo" class="btn-secondary" style="margin-left:8px;">try the demo</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</div>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
